<div id="p157" class="blockpost rowodd">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#11&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=157#p157">07-Sep-2009,Mon 09:02:49</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=3">higopi</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Expert Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"><img src="img/avatars/3.jpg" width="60" height="60" alt="" /></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: Need help in Transliteration</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>You missed out Vowel suffixes like below:<br /><br /></p><div class="codebox"><div class="incqbox"><h4>Code:</h4><div class="scrollbox" style="height: 9em"><pre>_transDic.Add('&#2367;', &quot;i&quot;);    // character \u093f
_transDic.Add('&#2368;', &quot;Ii&quot;);  //  character \u0940
_transDic.Add('&#2369;', &quot;u&quot;);   // character  \u0941
_transDic.Add('&#2370;', &quot;Uu&quot;); // character  \u0942</pre></div></div></div><p>Add like this for every vowel suffix. Also, you need to find a way to differentiate and handle the true Consonant like '&#2325;&#8204;' = K and Consonant+'a' Vowel combination like '&#2325;&#8204;' = 'Ka'. Because the literal is same for both.<br /><br />You can use <a href="http://rishida.net/tools/conversion/">http://rishida.net/tools/conversion/</a> for splitting out the vowel suffixes from&nbsp; Consonant+Vowel suffix combination</p>
					<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by higopi (07-Sep-2009,Mon 09:04:42)</em></p>
				</div>
				<div class="postsignature"><hr />Thanks,<br /><br />Gopi<br />Pick any two of &quot;Quality, Quick, Cheap&quot; service from me.</div>
			</div>
